Pre-requisites
a. Working installation of pentaho biserver-ce-3.8.0-stable
JNDI Configuration - Pentaho Data Integration (necessary on developer machine only)

* Edit the $PDI_HOME/biserver-ce/pentaho-solutions/system/simple-jndi/jdbc.properties file and append the contents of the fragment in configuration fragments folder.  


JNDI configuration - Pentaho BI 

* Edit the $PENTAHO_BI_HOME/biserver-ce/tomcat/webapps/pentaho/WEB-INF/web.xml and append the content of configuration fragment 'web.xml-fragment'. Modify the property values as necessary. 

* change the param-value for the param-name 'fully-qualified-server-url' in the web.xml. 
      eg.    <param-value>http://motechghana.org:8080/pentaho/</param-value>

* Edit the $PENTAHO_BI_HOME/tomcat/conf/context.xml and append the content of the configuration fragment 'context.xml-fragment' after the 'manager' element. Modify the propery values as necessary. 

* Edit $PENTAHO_BI_HOME/pentaho-solutions/system/simple-jndi/jdbc.properties and append the content of configuration fragment  'jdbc.properties-fragment'. 

To install the MoTeCH Business Intelligence system
1. Run motech_dw.sql to create the database for the data warehouse
2. Copy/symlink motech-bi-solution to the pentaho solutions directory
    ln -s ~/motech-bi/motech-bi-solution ./motech-bi-solution


